---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const meta = {
  title: "Programmatic SEO Services",
  description:
    "Design and ship data‑driven page systems that scale long‑tail visibility safely, with strong templates, internal linking, and schema.",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
  <article class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h1 class="title text-gradient">Programmatic SEO</h1>
    <img
      src="https://placehold.co/1200x630?text=Programmatic+SEO"
      alt="Programmatic SEO placeholder"
      class="mb-6 w-full rounded"
      width="1200"
      height="630"
      loading="lazy"
    />

    <p>
      Programmatic SEO turns your structured data (inventory, locations, services, comparisons, FAQs, jobs, and more)
      into hundreds or thousands of high‑quality, uniquely useful pages. Each page follows a research‑backed template,
      enriched with dynamic content modules, internal links, and schema—so you capture long‑tail demand at scale
      without creating index bloat.
    </p>

    <h2>When To Use It</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You have a growing dataset with repeatable search intent (e.g., cities, products, categories, features).</li>
      <li>You need consistent, high‑coverage landing pages that are better than “just another template.”</li>
      <li>You want growth that compounds with new data, not only new copy.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Deliverables</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Information architecture and URL patterns that scale cleanly.</li>
      <li>Page templates mapped to intents (browse, compare, detail, location, FAQ).</li>
      <li>Internal linking graph to surface the most valuable pages.</li>
      <li>Structured data (Schema.org) for eligible rich results.</li>
      <li>Guardrails to avoid duplication, doorway pages, and thin content.</li>
      <li>Monitoring dashboards to validate indexation and growth.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How I Build It</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Data audit and intent research.</li>
      <li>Template design with unique value elements and content safeguards.</li>
      <li>Technical spec: routing, canonical rules, pagination, and sitemaps.</li>
      <li>Implementation with your stack (headless CMS, DB, or static pre‑gen).</li>
      <li>QA, monitoring, and iteration based on performance signals.</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary">Request Programmatic SEO Assessment</a>
    </div>
  </article>
</PageLayout>
